<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to the Presidents Special
                                    Assistant</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-21">May 21,
                                    1943</date>.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Hopkins</hi>. I should be glad if you could
                                show this to the President. <pb facs="0401" n="299" xml:id="pg_299"/> I think the Chinese ought to be told to lay off this aggressive
                                policy while they themselves are so dependent on the help of
                                    others.<note n="1" xml:id="d109fn1">Regarding Churchill’s
                                    concern over Chinese policy toward Tibet, see his remarks during
                                    the meeting of the Pacific War Council, May 20, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_138">p.
                                    138</ref>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>W[<hi rend="smallcaps">inston</hi>| S C[<hi rend="smallcaps">hurchill</hi>]</signed>
                                <lb/> 21.5.43</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>